NEXUS: "Now that we know our position, we must verify connectivity to other
       station systems. I'm detecting intermittent failures across the network.
       Use ICMP echo requests - what humans call 'ping' - to test which systems
       are reachable from your workstation."

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

OBJECTIVE
═════════
The 'ping' command sends ICMP echo requests to test basic network connectivity.
It tells us:
  - Whether a host is reachable
  - How long packets take to travel (round-trip time)
  - If any packets are being lost

Test connectivity to critical station systems and understand the network
isolation boundaries that protect our sensitive systems.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASKS
═════

[ ] Task 1: Ping by IP Address
    Command: ping -c 4 172.20.0.20
    Send 4 packets to the server. Check for 0% packet loss.

[ ] Task 2: Ping by Hostname
    Command: ping -c 4 server
    Verify DNS resolution is working by pinging using the name.

[ ] Task 3: Test Cross-Network Isolation
    Command: ping -c 2 database
    Attempt to reach the backend database. This should FAIL.

[ ] Task 4: Verify API Gateway Connectivity
    Command: ping -c 2 api
    The API container bridges networks. This should succeed.

[ ] Task 5: Test Nonexistent Host
    Command: ping -c 2 172.20.0.250
    Understand the difference between DNS failure and connectivity failure.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

KEY CONCEPTS
════════════
  ping -c N    - Send N packets then stop
  0% loss      - All packets returned (healthy connection)
  100% loss    - No packets returned (host unreachable)
  RTT (ms)     - Round-trip time in milliseconds

FAILURE TYPES:
  "Name not known"     - DNS cannot resolve the hostname
  "No route to host"   - Network path does not exist
  No response          - Host down or firewall blocking

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

VERIFICATION
════════════
Create a file called 'ping_results.txt' with two lines:
  Line 1: A hostname you CAN reach (server or api)
  Line 2: The reason you CANNOT reach the database (isolation, firewall, or noroute)

Run: ./verify

Success: You understand which systems are reachable and why the database is
isolated. Network isolation is a security feature, not a failure!

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

